Morris Public Schools is pleased to announce as of September 1, 2020, anyone 18 years and under can receive free breakfast and lunch meals provided by the Child Nutrition Program. This includes all of our students, traditional and virtual. Anyone not physically attending classes must call 918-733-9072 ext. 298 in advance stating the number breakfasts and lunches desired. All account balances remain as is, until further notice.

In short, there will be no charges for meals for anyone 18 and under. If you have questions, call 918-733-9072 ext. 209.

Hot Spot Update:

We have all providers in except for AT&T which is supposed to be in Thursday or Friday.

If you can, come to the superintendent's office to pick up a hotspot. If you do not know what provider, you can tell us where you live and we can, in most cases, figure out what will work best.

You can also send an email to ckarch@morrisschools.net; just provide student names and grades, parent name and phone number, physical address, and if you know what provider works best, include that information as well.

Those of you who have requested ATT, I will send them home as soon as they arrive.

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians:

I regret to inform you that a member of our varsity football team has tested positive for COVID. The last exposure to our team and coaches was Monday, August 24th. After visiting with the Okmulgee County Health Department, all members of the varsity football team and coaching staff will have to undergo quarantine until September 8th. Our football student athletes will have to do distance learning during this time. Testing is offered through the Okmulgee County Health Department. If you have a student who becomes ill, please notify the high school office and keep us informed of the situation. Scrimmages scheduled for this Friday night have been cancelled as well as games scheduled on September 4th and 11th.

Sincerely,

Dr. Chris Karch, Superintendent

As we prepare for the return of full-time students to our campus, GCTC‚Äôs top priority is the safety and well being of our students, teachers, staff and all stakeholders. With that in mind, PHASE IV of our Mitigation Plan will follow the guidelines provided by the CDC as well as the Oklahoma State Department of Health‚Äôs COVID-19 Alert System.

PHASE IV will include all prior Phases I, II & III with the addition of the new Return to Learn Plans and guidelines which can be found on our website.

- GCTC‚ÄôS COVID-19 Alert System color chart
- Student Guide Return to Learning ‚Äì GREEN (New Normal)
- Student Guide Return to Learning ‚Äì YELLOW (Low Risk)
- Student Guide Return to Learning ‚Äì ORANGE (Moderate Risk)
- Student Guide Return to Learning ‚Äì RED (High Risk)

Please note, when full-time classes begin on August 24, our school will begin in the ORANGE ZONE.

Please refer to our website for downloadable documents and details.

post_text:
Morris Elementary device checkout for students who signed up for the virtual path is scheduled for Tuesday, August 18 from 2:00 PM to 5:00 PM.

This is for students who chose to do the virtual approach with Morris Elementary. The device issued will be as follows:

Pre-K and Kindergarten will have an IPAD checked out to the student through the library.
First Grade through fifth grade will have a chromebook checked to the students through the library.

There will be a few documents for you to fill out regarding the checkout of the device. You will also receive the syllabus regarding virtual learning as well as any textbooks you will need and school issued supplies for your student.

Please enter the building through the main entrance of the elementary. You will then exit through the north doors of the lower elementary. Please remember social distancing will be followed. Thank you for your help. Morris Elementary is a great place to learn virtually too!

Please remember the first day of virtual learning will be August 27th!

Dear Morris School Community:

I have decided to postpone the opening of school until August 27th. Several things have factored into this decision. The greatest two factors are that the elementary school construction is not completed and we are still waiting for delivery of technology and other supplies that are going to be required for us to return. PK will also start on the 27th. Staff inservice dates will remain August 17-19. Staff will be receiving a schedule this afternoon. Thank you for your continued support and understanding.

Dr. Karch

post_text: If you are interested in signing up for summer driver's ed, you will need to sign up by this Wednesday, March 11th. There is a $100 fee for students enrolled at Morris School and a $300 fee for all others. The fee is due at the time you sign up. There are 48 slots open this year and it will be on a first come first served basis. Take your signup fee to Stephanie Klimek in the Superintendent's office. She will write you a receipt. Bring your receipt to the high school office to sign up on the list. You must be 15 years old by May 15th to take drivers ed.

Dear Community Members:

We have recently been made aware of a company that is soliciting in the name of Morris Public Schools. This company is "Sports Promotion Network" based in Arlington, Texas. They have not asked for permission and to our knowledge, Morris Public Schools is not receiving any financial support from this company. So please do not contribute. This is a scam and you can read about the company in the link below.

https://www.columbiadailyherald.com/advertisernews/20181017/texas-based-promotion-company-allegedly-scamming-wilco-businesses

If you ever have any questions about anyone soliciting in the name of Morris Public Schools, please contact us prior to doing business with that party.

Thank you,

Morris Public Schools

Morris Public Schools has used a service in the past called SchoolWay for school notifications, emergency notifications and school closing notifications. The company that provided this service to us is no longer offering it at this time.
MPS is now using E-Notes Notification Center.
To sign up for this notification service, go to our school web page and scroll down to the lower right of the screen towards the bottom of the page. Click on E-Notes Notification. Click on the blue link labeled Please sign up today. You will then be able to create your account. Once your account has been created and verified, you can then choose from the list of subscriptions you would like to subscribe to. There are many subscriptions to choose from and you can subscribe to more than one.

https://morrisschools.net/

To Parents and Guardians of Morris Public Schools,

Morris Public Schools is saddened by the loss of one of its employees, Becky Reilly on Monday, April 15, 2019. Becky Reilly worked as a paraprofessional for Morris Elementary since 2002.

She took pride in coming to work everyday and impacting students lives. She also touched employees with her gracious heart and commitment to education.

There will be counselors available if any student is in need of services with coping during this time. Please continue to keep the Reilly family in your hearts and prayers.

Morris Public Schools Family

Morris Open Transfer

Morris Public Schools is now accepting applications for open transfer for the 2019-2020 school year. Currently, we have openings in several grades. We will be reviewing applications as they are received in the office. To optimize opportunity of an approved application, we ask you apply for a transfer as soon as possible. You may pick up an application packet at the superintendent's office or online through the link on our school website. Morris Public Schools * 307 South 6th Street * Morris, OK 74445

January 15, 2019 at 11:15 PM ¬∑

Morris Band Boosters are excited to start the "12 Months of Flowers" fundraiser today, sponsored by Morris Bands and Morris' own Hometown Treasures! For a 2 week period starting today, you can purchase a floral discount form for $30 and receive a small bouquet of flowers every month for a year! You simply stop into Hometown Treasures, have your card punched, and pick up the flowers! Who doesn't love fresh flowers! Plus, by purchasing the floral discount, you are helping the band program and supporting local small business at the same time! Leave a comment also if you are interested and we'll make sure someone gets a card to you!

Diana Weaver Force‚ÄéMorris, OK Band Boosters
January 15, 2019 at 11:15 PM ¬∑

Morris Band Boosters are excited to start the "12 Months of Flowers" fundraiser today, sponsored by Morris Bands and Morris' own Hometown Treasures! For a 2 week period starting today, you can purchase a floral discount form for $30 and receive a small bouquet of flowers every month for a year! You simply stop into Hometown Treasures, have your card punched, and pick up the flowers! Who doesn't love fresh flowers! Plus, by purchasing the floral discount, you are helping the band program and supporting local small business at the same time! Leave a comment also if you are interested and we'll make sure someone gets a card to you!

FFA
This Saturday January 12th, 10am at the Animal Science facility, Morris FFA and 4-H Booster Club will be hosting a local livestock show for all Morris FFA and 4-H students who show livestock. The Morris FFA and 4-H Booster Club would like to invite out the community to enjoy the show and lunch. Show order will be as follows:
Swine
Sheep
Goats
Heifers
Steers
Weigh cards for pigs, sheep, and goats will be due at 9 with show starting at 10. Cattle entries will be due by 10. We will break at 12 for lunch. Everyone is welcome and we will be serving Hot Dogs and Frito Chili Pie to everyone that attends.

Morris Public Schools
November 5, 2018 at 3:08 PM ¬∑

MORRIS PUBLIC SCHOOLS HONORS VETERANS DAY

Morris Public Schools will be honoring Veterans on November 9 with many activities. The district would like to invite any Veteran to attend. The activities are listed below:

Morris Elementary will be celebrating Veterans Day on Friday, November 9 @ 8:10 in the Elementary Gym. If Veterans could arrive at 8:00 at the elementary. There will be free donuts and coffee available for you.

Pack 287 will be presenting the Colors.

Morris Middle School will be having an assembly at 11:15 in the auditorium. There will also be a free luncheon for Veterans immediately following the assembly at the Middle School.

If you are planning on attending the luncheon, please RSVP with the Morris Middle School office at 918-733-9072 EXT. 271.

Morris High School will be having a Veterans Assembly at 12:00 in the Middle School auditorium.

Special thanks for your service to the United States of America. We are truly grateful! We hope you can attend Friday, November 9.

Sincerely,
Morris Public Schools Staff
Morris Public Schools Students

post_text:
FAFSA OPENS 10/1/2018

The FAFSA should be completed as soon as possible after Oct. 1 to ensure priority consideration for some types of financial aid. Students can prepare by gathering their information now. Since the 2018-19 FAFSA requires applicants to use 2016 tax information, they can use their 2016 return to complete the application at FAFSA.gov right away! There will be no need to wait.

Also, to complete and submit the FAFSA online, students and one of their parents/guardians will each need to create a FSA ID (Federal Student Aid ID) at FSAID.ed.gov. This username/password serves as a signature on the FAFSA and student loan applications, and allows them to access other federal aid websites. It‚Äôs beneficial for families to create their FSA IDs before starting the FAFSA form at FAFSA.gov to speed up the application process.

http://tinyurl.com/y9kvkwkb
